#DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - For 20-years, the Esigodini community in KwaZulu-Natal has asked government for a school to be built in their village. Currently, pupils have to travel at least 25 kilometres through a snake-infested forest to the nearest school but when - if ever - will their pleas be heard? eNCA’s Lethiwe Mdluli finds out in the video. 